 A man has been jailed for 30 years after he was found guilty of chopping off his cousin’s hand. ALSO READ:

Couple acquitted of murder Jackson Musila Musonye was found guilty of hacking Wycliffe Shitemi's hand in Shibuye village in Kakamega East District on October 24, 2017. Delivering his judgement on Friday, Senior Resident Magistrate Erick Malesi said the prosecution had proved its case against the accused. The court heard that Mr Musonye committed the offence due to a land tussle. The complainant, whose right hand is now a stump just below the elbow, was said to have been defending himself from the accused. Musonye was given 14 days to lodge an appeal. Avoid fake news! Subscribe to the Standard SMS service and receive factual, verified breaking news as it happens. Text the word 'NEWS' to 22840